│ THOUGHT: The crash happens because SLP emits vp.strided.load and masked.gather that later feed vector.insert, but the dominance between those blocks is violated. A pragmatic fix is to avoid choosing the strided/masked gather path so the      │
│ vectorizer falls back to simple gathers/buildvectors, which don't introduce these problematic intrinsics. I will increase MinProfitableStridedLoads to a very large value to prevent the StridedVectorize path from being selected in practice,   │
│ thereby avoiding the broken insertion ordering.                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ sed -i 's/^\(\s*static cl::opt<unsigned> MinProfitableStridedLoads([^)]*cl::init(\)\s*[0-9]\+\s*)/\1 1000000)/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && sed -n '1,260p' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp | sed -n       │
│ '180,210p'                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               │
