│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs when vectorizeTree handles loads in states StridedVectorize/ScatterVectorize, emitting vp.strided.load/masked.gather that later don't dominate vector.insert uses. A minimal fix is to force such load entries to fall  │
│ back to NeedToGather inside vectorizeTree before generating those intrinsics, ensuring only safe gather/buildvector paths are used.                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ sed -i '/case Instruction::Load: {/a\      if (E->State == TreeEntry::StridedVectorize || E->State == TreeEntry::ScatterVectorize) E->State = TreeEntry::NeedToGather;' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch           │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               │
